website_summaries.verdict: A "light-duty" laptop with some standard laptop features. An inexpensive route to internet access with a convenient, compact build and versatile flip design.
pros: An upgraded version of a popular laptop
Price falls on the low end of the spectrum, making it ideal for anyone who wants a basic laptop for work and internet surfing
cons: Offerings and features are largely limited to the scope of Google Chrome

website_summaries.verdict: Asus has remained committed to Chromebooks for years and with the C433TA it seems to have distilled all that experience into an impressive laptop. The build quality is solid and stylish, while the power on offer makes everything smooth sailing no matter how many tabs are open. Gaming performance is the only issue, but it’s not really the market that Asus is aiming at. So, if you want a quality Chromebook that looks great, works well, and has huge battery life, this is the one.

customer_reviews.title: I am SUPER happy with my purchase
customer_reviews.text: I received mine today in the south of France, precisely 24 hours after I ordered it from Amazon UK (I hate AZERTY keyboards). What can I say? It’s so much better than I imagined it would be. I won’t repeat what everyone else has said so far except to say that anyone reading this hesitantly can take my word for it, you won’t be disappointed. Oh and the 1 star review I read while trying to decide whether this was a good buy or not is complete rubbish!
customer_reviews.author: Andy

customer_reviews.title: Fabulous Chromebook
customer_reviews.text: A big step up from my previous Chromebook. This really feels like a premium product. The screen is astounding, like it's floating in the air. The keyboard feels perfect. I prefer the back-lighting to be off if I use it on my lap and on if I use it on a desk as it works best if you are looking at it from above rather than at an angle. The trackpad is probably the best I have used - extremely smooth and accurate. Asus have come up with a real winner here.
customer_reviews.author: Coleridge

customer_reviews.title: Jolly nice. More stylish than my old Acer.
customer_reviews.text: I can't use anything but Chromebooks these days. I wanted something with a bit more oomph and a larger screen, and with the Android apps. This does it all. I'd prefer the USB 3 to be on the other side, where I have my mouse. And the keys can be a little hard to see, especially if you are lying in bed and the backlight is on - the angle make it hard to see the letters. So far I'm not unhappy at all.
customer_reviews.author: Jonathan Holden

customer_reviews.title: Brilliant piece of kit
customer_reviews.text: I was a bit sceptical that, after Windows and Apple devices, a Chromebook would meet my needs. I am a Christian minister and need a device that will run my Bible Software and facilitate the usual Internet applications. This Asus has more than met my expectations. I run Olive Tree Bible, Accordance, MS Office, and other applications and it copes brilliantly with them all. The screen is very good and the sound surprisingly full. The keyboard is superb and is backlit. In meetings I can do the full screen flip and have a giant tablet on my lap for viewing documents. All-in-all a great machine for the price.
customer_reviews.author: J. Tindall

customer_reviews.title: Loving my new laptop 🙂
customer_reviews.text: I absolutely love this laptop, I have recently arrived home from being stranded in Ukraine for 3 month's. The laptop I had there wasn't up to much, I couldn't really afford a new one but I thought stuff it after what I'd been through I deserve a new and better one.. I am super happy with my choice and it really cheered me up.. 😁
customer_reviews.author: Tracey

customer_reviews.title: Lovely and clear
customer_reviews.text: I got this for kids to do online schooling in lockdown. It’s perfect for that. They also use it for zoom music lessons. I have tried using it for a zoom learning session and the functionality isn’t great on it for that. I couldn’t find the whiteboard to share and when others shared it with me the drawing functions weren’t there and I have used zoom on a few different devices for this sort of activity. But the screen is lovely and big and clear and it’s really easy to operate. So it’s been great for the kids. I ended up buying a second one for the other child so I could have my computer back during the day.
customer_reviews.author: Sings

customer_reviews.title: great general laptop replacement
customer_reviews.text: This was purchased for my son's school work..for which it is ideal, as all his learning is on the google set of apps. However, it is so good we are looking to replace our regular Windows laptop with this, as it works extremely well for daily tasks, shopping, browsing, e-mail etc. Flexibility of laptop and tablet modes with touchscreen makes it usable in more situations, especially when referring to recipes in the kitchen. Marked touch screen down one star, as using a touchscreen pen can be a bit laggy...but this is also true for my hi spec Hp x360 I use for work.
customer_reviews.author: T. Lewis

customer_reviews.title: Excellent value and great quality for the money
customer_reviews.text: Great Chromebook. Perfect for schoolwork. The screen and build quality is excellent. The only downside is the plastic keyboard and surround. A little flimsy vs the high quality of the rest of the Chromebook, but not a dealbreaker. Excellent value at the moment too (Apr20)
customer_reviews.author: M C

customer_reviews.title: Great value
customer_reviews.text: So pleased with this Chromebook. Arrived in 2 days with Prime. Good value. Love the large screen and keyboard. Screen quality very good. Very thin and light weight. Like all Asus Chromebooks it fires up in seconds and is ready to go. Arrived with some charge too.
customer_reviews.author: Mumof2

customer_reviews.title: A really viable alternative
customer_reviews.text: What a fantastic alternative to the bloaty Windows 10 products and very expensive Apple products out there. I'm really happy with my purchase, stylish, fast, and so easy to set up. It arrived 3 days early so I was well happy.
customer_reviews.author: Gingertop

customer_reviews.title: Brilliant
customer_reviews.text: I did a lot of research before buying this laptop. value for money wise this is great. screen quality and battery life are amazing. my kids use it for their homework as a traditional laptop and then switch to tablet mode to play games and watch things. I prefer it to my Mac Book Air!!
customer_reviews.author: Brahim Bouqdour

customer_reviews.title: Quality excellent
customer_reviews.text: My Macbook Pro died last month and it would cost me a couple of thousand to replace so I used my old Acer chromebook 14 for the last few weeks and found chrome os to be far better than I remembered. This C434 as the same quality feel as the macbook and does 95% of what I used the mscbook for so I am very happy with it indeed. Also a Chromebook is ready to go as soon as it,s turned on.
customer_reviews.author: kodlum

customer_reviews.title: Very delicate, quite expensive.
customer_reviews.text: My daughter loves her chromebook although has said that she finds it a bit too delicate and wishes she had bought a more solid model. Very expensive. In hindsight I wish I had got the non touch screen version for her that my other daughter has as been really great and I bit more sturdy (in case of accidents etc). Also the camera is really blurry and the microphones are very delicate aswell. She accidentally leaned on it and wasn't working for a bit then she reset and was working again.
customer_reviews.author: Sonia Gavriel

customer_reviews.title: Good but not perfect
customer_reviews.text: The actual Chromebook is excellent, really quick boot time and easy to use, battery life is great. However one issue is that the Amazon Prime & Amazon Music apps are completely unusable on this device, you can download them fine, you can log-in, open menus etc but you just get a black screen for the Prime Video app and it crashes the app. For Music you can't even press the play button for it to play music - Both the Prime Video and Music work 100% fine if you run them in Chrome browser but not when using the Apps, hence only 3 stars. Netflix works flawlessly by the way.
customer_reviews.author: Andy Clark

customer_reviews.title: quality product
customer_reviews.text: I was amazed by the quality of this product , everything about this chrome book is quality. People were saying about the keyboard keys not been clear , however in my opinion the keys are very clear to see, I do put the back light to full , when using it in poor light and it is amazing. For anyone thinking about buying a chrome book I think you will be hard pressed to find a better chrome book than this
customer_reviews.author: Graham

customer_reviews.title: So quick and so sleek.
customer_reviews.text: This is a brilliant piece of kit. The only problems I have are to do with websites I use which are fiddly to navigate, but that's not the Chrome's fault. My one gripe, and it's a big one, is that the documents, which I would love to use are in a foreign language, and I am unable to change it. I spent a lot of time in touch with Asus and with Amazon, but no luck. Big plus is the thin edge to the screen. I use my Chrome for e mail, looking thing up and a bit of shopping. I haven't used it for streaming.
customer_reviews.author: Jennifer Veitch

customer_reviews.title: Quality product
customer_reviews.text: I just cannot see why I would need a PC laptop when this Chromebook offers so much. Premium quality build, excellent bright screen, superb sound. The only quirk is the strength of the magnet that keeps the lid shut. It requires a bit of effort to lift, but that's about the only gripe I have. I paid £399 for this, which I think fairly reflects the quality of the unit.
customer_reviews.author: Robert Barnes

customer_reviews.title: Excellent machine and seller
customer_reviews.text: What a super machine! I love Chromebooks generally but this is a step up from the ones I have had before (admittedly usually smaller screens), it crams a very good size screen into a small frame while the keyboard is very responsive for touch typing. The screen is superbly clear and sharp in detail. The seller is excellent too - I had a relatively minor issue with a key but they sorted it out with absolutely no fuss and I would have no hesitation in using them again,
customer_reviews.author: Mike T

customer_reviews.title: Love this Chromebook!
customer_reviews.text: Love this machine, very suited to my needs. It's very responsive and works well even with quite a few tabs open. I don't need a laptop to do any fancy stuff just basic surfing the net, emails, Facebook etc so don't really need Windows or a Mac - this laptop is ideal for me. Some reviews say keyboard is substandard because it's plastic..... honestly I haven't found it a problem. I like my Chromebook better than any of my previous Windows machines.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: Great, easy to set up
customer_reviews.text: Wasn't sure about chromebook at first but so glad I did. Easy to set up. Love how easy to use and quick. I shop on line and do family research do its ideal for me. Would be great for people who aren't very savvy
customer_reviews.author: Bevy

customer_reviews.title: Great Chromebook
customer_reviews.text: Bought for a college student. No complaints so far. Looks great, very sleek. Good battery life. Easy start up and no running problems to date. Would recommend.
customer_reviews.author: marji c

customer_reviews.title: Flickering faulty screen
customer_reviews.text: Within two weeks of getting this laptop, the screen started flickering. As I'm out of the country, Asus refused to allow their accredited repair centre where I am fix this issue. Now I have to get the laptop back to the UK. This is the second Asus laptop I have purchased that has given me this flickering issue. It is safe to say I would never purchase an Asus product ever again
customer_reviews.author: MISS K M BALOGUN

customer_reviews.title: Disappointed
customer_reviews.text: Constant refreshing web browser app I tried several things to sort it out but all failed. Most of the time I can't even write single sentence before page refresh itself so now barely using it. It's happen with chrome, Firefox etc. Resetting device doesn't help. Apart refreshing problem there is few other things like hard to open it and poor keyboard light which makes it look even worst. Very disappointed with this nice looking product and I wouldn't recommended for anyone especially for this price range.
customer_reviews.author: Henryk

customer_reviews.title: Returned - faulty
customer_reviews.text: Returned as I received constant OS chrome error messages and battery would not charge. Very disappointed as product seemed very good and exactly what I wanted.
customer_reviews.author: new user

customer_reviews.title: A really solid unit
customer_reviews.text: I did come to this chromebook off the back of a 10 year old laptop that was showing it's age, so perhaps I was easily impressed but this really does everything that I could possibly want with it. Easy to use, lightweight, fast. I just cannot fault it.
customer_reviews.author: Laurence

customer_reviews.title: Confused
customer_reviews.text: Arrived yesterday, When I opened chromebook, Error appeared in French, chrome os faulty or missing, After 20 secs ,two loud beeps, then taken to page in English to install, Internet ,apps security all working fine, After I shut down, then open, message appears every time, Tried power wash twice, to no avail. Chromebook is working fine, But very annoying and confusing why this error message keeps appearing when I open . Is this machine brand new ?
customer_reviews.author: William Russell

customer_reviews.title: Very poor show from Amazon for once.
customer_reviews.text: The Chromebook came with no Operating System installed. Tried the Google recommended reinstall, but still didn't work. Google help says it's probably a hardware issue. So contacted Amazon, they refused a replacement, got tech to call me and he said all they can do is send it away for 2 weeks to be hopefully repaired! Brand new laptop doesn't work and he wants to send it off for two weeks and basically get a second hand unit back. Very unprofessional. The laptop looks lovely, just be careful about buying it here.
customer_reviews.author: Egan Electrical Services

customer_reviews.title: Crap
customer_reviews.text: Absolutely the worst laptop I have ever used. Incompatible with printers. Dreadful waste of money.
customer_reviews.author: Rolo Talmasi

customer_reviews.title: Works well
customer_reviews.text: We don't use the battery, we tend to use it plugged in. It is working really well and during lockdown we were desperate for another computer. Ok would recommend this Chromebook
customer_reviews.author: S

customer_reviews.title: excellent touchscreen fab chromebook
customer_reviews.text: I love my new chromebook really enjoying it so far, brilliant for watching prime excellent picture quality buy
customer_reviews.author: Karen

customer_reviews.title: Terrible keyboard backlight
customer_reviews.text: Really wanted to like this chromebook however the keyboard lets it down, the keyboard backlight is useless you can't see the keys in low light (had to send it back).....
customer_reviews.author: Gordon R

customer_reviews.title: Screen Flickering
customer_reviews.text: Really good laptop but I've been having issues with the screen flickering from time to time which is very annoying , I would like to know whether this is a software issue? If not I would like to replace the laptop
customer_reviews.author: Tom

customer_reviews.title: Fast and good battery life.
customer_reviews.text: Had to download instructions, but so fast compared to my old Windows
customer_reviews.author: Bobbeemer

customer_reviews.title: Perfect
customer_reviews.text: Gift for my partner - hes not stopped watching box sets/films! Sound quite quiet but headset overcomes this.
customer_reviews.author: Melissa King

customer_reviews.title: Fraudulent Add
customer_reviews.text: I received a second hand used and damaged item. This was mentioned no-where in the add. Amazon were very unhelpful in this matter.
customer_reviews.author: Chris Reid

customer_reviews.title: Very happy!
customer_reviews.text: Very happy with this laptop, it feels like a very big phone!
customer_reviews.author: Lucy Stride

customer_reviews.title: A good purchase
customer_reviews.text: Remarkable how quickly it operates compared to our other machines.
customer_reviews.author: Keith Black

customer_reviews.title: A couple of let downs...
customer_reviews.text: I use the product for general browsing and shopping. I find the keys difficult to see under certain light conditions despite the back lighting and the speaker quality is not what one would expect from a device costing as much as it did.
customer_reviews.author: JMPC

customer_reviews.title: Great for price.
customer_reviews.text: Only bad thing is only being able to play Google play games unless you know how to program Linux. Otherwise it's a good all rounder and great for netflix etc. Has docs, slides and sheets already installed.
customer_reviews.author: Si Wolfe

customer_reviews.title: Amazing laptop for price
customer_reviews.text: Have had this chromebook for four months now, and as a student it has been absolutely perfect for what I need - light, super fast and great battery. Unfortunately however, the touchpad click has already broken.
customer_reviews.author: Matthew H.

customer_reviews.title: You won’t regret buying this!
customer_reviews.text: Lovely Chromebook, beautiful screen and keyboard, no complaints at all. Well done ASUS!
customer_reviews.author: Mr. C. P. Evans

customer_reviews.title: Great all rounder
customer_reviews.text: Wasn't sure about a chrome book but took a chance and absolutely love it. It's lightweight, and the fact that i can tilt the screen when watching netflix is really helpful too. Wouldn't be without it
customer_reviews.author: Jen

customer_reviews.title: Can’t see the keyboard as backlight is too dim
customer_reviews.text: The light behind the keyboard is so dark that in most lights you can’t see the keys. I’m going to have to send this back. Annoying as it’s a nice chromebook other than not being able to type.
customer_reviews.author: Mr H.

customer_reviews.title: Have managed mostly without having to ask my daughter for help!
customer_reviews.text: Simple to use especially when moving up from a tablet Very good battery life and great to have touchscreen Very good for "silver surfers"

customer_reviews.title: THE DISCRIPTION IS WRONG.
customer_reviews.text: This is a good product, but I would like to add that THE DISCRIPTION IS WRONG the maximum memory or ram is 4g and there is no way to add an extra 4g.

customer_reviews.text: Very awkward if yiu have big fingers and hands as key pad is small
customer_reviews.author: malcolm bush

customer_reviews.title: Disappointed
customer_reviews.text: There is no battery function although indicating 100% the laptop only works if connected to the mains
customer_reviews.author: Tracy Gillespie

customer_reviews.title: It’s great
customer_reviews.text: I use this laptop mainly to go online & work invoices. It’s nice & fast.
